{
  "texts": [
    "A number of high-profile incidents in recent years demonstrate their disruptive potential:",
    "During the Russian invasion of Ukraine, a fabricated video emerged online in March 2022 that depicted Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy apparently urging his troops to lay down their arms and surrender.",
    "This video, a deepfake, was cleverly edited into a social media broadcast format and spread rapidly on Facebook and other platforms before being debunked.",
    "Had it been widely believed, it could have eroded military morale and undermined public trust in official communications during a critical national crisis.",
    "Ukrainian news outlets and government spokespeople rushed to clarify that the video was fake, illustrating both the risk and the swift response such disinformation provokes (U.S. Department of State, 2024)."
  ]
}